Prerequisites

- GNU Make
- bash

Installation

- Download the archive
- Unpack. For example in /opt/moa
- Set the following environment vars (globally! For example in 
  /etc/profile or /etc/profile.d/moa.sh):
	- MOABASE=/opt/moa
	- PATH=$PATH:/opt/moa/bin
- Set permissions, assuming all users on this machine are allowed
  to use Moa.
	- chmod -R a+rX /opt/moa
	- chmod a+rx /opt/moa/bin/*
	- chmod a+rw /opt/moa/var
- Check if weka works, run:
	- weka ls
  this should come back without an error message, and the following
  file should be created:
  	- /opt/moa/var/weka.db
  	
  
	
